c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Fellow is best suited for managers, meeting heavy teams, leadership, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Taskade, meanwhile, shines for remote teams, AI enthusiasts, small teams, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, Fellow describes itself as \"AI meeting management platform for agendas, notes, and action items.\" Taskade, established in 2017, positions itself as \"AI-powered workspace with custom AI agents for tasks, notes, and projects.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Fellow** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (10 vs 9), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Taskade is a poor choice — far from it. Taskade excels in its own right, particularly for remote teams and AI enthusiasts.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent meeting note templates, go with Fellow. If custom ai agents for different workflows matters more to you, Taskade is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
